

                  Node & Express -server / back end technology
                -------------------------------------

    Basic commands
    **************
    1. create package.json :   npm init

    2. install express : npm i express

    3. install JWT Token : npm i jsonwebtoken

    4. install mongoose : npm i mongoose

    4. install cors : npm i cors






    Basic steps
    ***********

    1. create package.json

    2. install express

    3. create index.js file

    4. import express

    5. server app creation using express

    6. set up port number for server

    7. Client HTTP request resolving

       server-app.HTTP-request(path,callback)

    8.Response status code
     **********************

     1xx - Information
     2xx - Success
     3xx - redirection
     4xx - client side error
     5xx - server side error



   9. JWT TOKEN - User validation

      9.1 Token generation

      9.2 Token validity



   10. Middleware :- 

       10.1 Application specific

       10.2 Router specific


   11.Mongo DB Connection

      11.1 Install mongoose

      11.2 create db.js file

      11.3 import mongoose in db.js

      11.4 state connection string using mongoose

      11.5 create model / collections

      11.6 export model




   12. Asynchronous function resolving  - promise

       12.1 resolved state -  .then()

       12.2 reject state   -   catch()



